//ldd:source ast.ly, modules.ly
//ldd:why "Defines all AST node types for the Lyric language. Leaf package — no dependencies on other bootstrap packages. Shared by parser, checker, desugar, and lowerer."

// ## Architecture
//
// The AST is a strict hierarchy rooted in File. A File contains one or more
// LyricBlock nodes. Data flows in from the parser; once constructed, the AST
// is the source of truth for the entire toolchain.
//
// Two file formats share the same AST:
// - .lyric: declaration-only (FuncDecl.body is null)
// - .ly: full implementation (FuncDecl.body is Block)

// ## Invariants — Nullable Variant Fields
//
// Lyric uses nullable fields per variant on class types instead of Go's
// any-typed Data fields + Kind enum. Expr has one nullable field per
// ExprKind (call: CallData?, bin_op: BinOpData?, etc.). Only the field
// matching `kind` is non-null.
//
// This is required because Lyric `any` maps to `void*` in C — no type
// recovery without casts. The nullable field pattern is verbose but
// fully type-safe in C.
//
// Applies to: Expr, Stmt, TypeExpr, Pattern.
//
// Exception: Expr.resolved_type is typed as TypeExpr? (not any). TypeExpr
// is defined earlier in the same file, so proper typing is possible.
//
// CRITICAL: When accessing variant data, always check null first. The
// pattern is: `if expr.call != null { let c = expr.call! ... }`.
// Do NOT assume a field is non-null based on kind without checking.

// ## Invariants — No If-Expressions
//
// Lyric does not support if-as-expression. All conditional assignment
// must use: let mut x = default; if cond { x = value }
// This affects match-as-expression too — use mutable variable + match statement.

// ## Invariants — Positions and Spans
//
// Every major AST node carries a Span (start Pos, end Pos). Pos has file,
// line, column. Required for error messages with precise source locations.

// ## Invariants — Expression and Statement Kinds
//
// ExprKind enum: Ident, IntLit, FloatLit, StringLit, StringInterp, BoolLit,
// Nil, Unary, Binary, Call, MethodCall, FieldAccess, Index, ListLit,
// TupleLit, MapLit, StructLit, Lambda, Match, Cast, Unwrap, Try, Slice, Is.
//
// StmtKind enum: VarDecl, Assign, Return, Expr, If, For, While, Match,
// Block, Cascade, Break, Continue, Spawn, Select, Lock, IfLet, LetElse.
//
// PatternKind enum: Ident, Literal, Variant, Wildcard, Tuple.
//
// TypeExprKind enum: Named, Optional, Union, Sequence, Map, Tuple, Func,
// Channel, Lock, Unit.

// ## Invariants — Relations
//
// RelationDecl models ownership (Owns) and reference (Refs) relationships.
// Supports cardinality (IsMany), labeled sides, and implementation hints.
// Relations generate fields and impl blocks during desugaring.

// ## Architecture — Transitive Stdlib Merge
//
// merge_stdlib uses a transitive closure algorithm:
// 1. Collect all type names and function calls used in user code
// 2. Find matching declarations in stdlib
// 3. Transitively follow references (if merged func returns a stdlib class, merge that class too)
// 4. Handle primitive extension methods (e.g. i32.get_hash) for generic code (Dict)
// 5. Repeat until no new dependencies discovered
// This avoids bloating the binary with unused stdlib code.

// ## Architecture — Module Resolution (Namespace Flattening)
//
// resolve_module_imports flattens packages into a single global namespace in 3 phases:
// 1. Prefixing: all declarations in imported package get prefix (e.g. math.sin → math_sin)
// 2. Internal rewriting: references within imported package updated to prefixed names
// 3. Qualified access rewriting: caller's math.sin(x) → math_sin(x)
// This is because the bootstrap compiler targets a flat compilation model.

// ## Invariants — Desugaring
//
// Five desugar passes run BEFORE the checker, in strict order:
// 1. InterfaceEmbeds — flatten embedded interfaces
// 2. InterfaceFields — field decls → getter/setter methods
// 3. Relations — inject ownership/reference fields + impl blocks
// 4. Destructors — copy interface destructor bodies to classes
// 5. DefaultImpls — extract interface methods to top-level functions
//
// Each pass creates AST consumed by later passes. Order is critical.

// BinaryOp = enum { Add, Sub, Mul, Div, Mod, Eq, Neq, Lt, Le, Gt, Ge, And, Or, BitAnd, BitOr, BitXor, Shl, Shr }

// ExprKind = enum { Ident(name: Sym), IntLit(value: string, type_hint: Sym?), FloatLit(value: string), StringLit(value: string), StringInterp(parts: [Expr]), BoolLit(value: bool), Nil, Call(func_expr: Expr, type_args: [TypeExpr], args: [Expr], mut_args: [bool]), MethodCall(receiver: Expr, method: Sym, type_args: [TypeExpr], args: [Expr], mut_args: [bool]), FieldAccess(receiver: Expr, field_name: Sym), Index(receiver: Expr, index: Expr), Slice(receiver: Expr, low: Expr?, high: Expr?), Unary(op: UnaryOp, operand: Expr), Binary(left: Expr, op: BinaryOp, right: Expr), TupleLit(elems: [Expr]), ListLit(elems: [Expr]), MapLit(keys: [Expr], values: [Expr]), StructLit(type_name: Sym, type_args: [TypeExpr], fields: [StructLitField]), Lambda(params: [Param], return_type: TypeExpr?, body: Block), Match(value: Expr, arms: [MatchArm]), Cast(target_type: TypeExpr, operand: Expr), Unwrap(operand: Expr), Try(operand: Expr), Is(operand: Expr, variant: Sym), IfElse(cond: Expr, then_block: Block, else_ifs: [ElseIf], else_block: Block) }

// ImplMappingKind = enum { Alias, FieldBind, Inline }

// PatternKind = enum { Ident(name: Sym), Literal(expr: Expr), Variant(name: Sym, bindings: [Pattern]), Wildcard, Tuple(elems: [Pattern]) }

// RelationKind = enum { Owns, Refs }

// StmtKind = enum { VarDecl(name: Sym, names: [Sym], type_expr: TypeExpr?, is_mut: bool, value: Expr?), Assign(target: Expr, value: Expr), Return(value: Expr?), ExprStmt(expr: Expr), If(condition: Expr, then_block: Block, else_ifs: [ElseIf], else_block: Block?), For(var_name: Sym, index_var: Sym?, collection: Expr, body: Block), While(condition: Expr, body: Block), Match(value: Expr, arms: [MatchArm]), BlockStmt(block: Block), Cascade(body: Block), Break, Continue, Spawn(body: Block), Select(cases: [SelectCase]), Yield(value: Expr?), Lock(mutex: Expr, body: Block), IfLet(pattern: Pattern, value: Expr, then_block: Block, else_block: Block?), LetElse(pattern: Pattern, value: Expr, else_block: Block) }

// TypeExprKind = enum { Named(name: Sym, args: [TypeExpr]), Optional(inner: TypeExpr), Union(variants: [TypeExpr]), Sequence(elem: TypeExpr), Map(key: TypeExpr, value: TypeExpr), Tuple(fields: [TupleField]), Func(params: [TypeExpr], ret: TypeExpr), Channel(elem: TypeExpr), Generator(elem: TypeExpr), Lock, Unit }

